cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a programming model for parallelization of dynamic algorithms. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the building blocks and abstractions used in the programming model. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses how data can be split into smaller pieces. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses how the programming model facilitates the development of high performance parallel back ends. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper discusses performance considerations and presents a pilot implementation with performance results.
